-- World Gold Council, Augmentum Spend $18.7 Million for BullionVault Stake
-- Claudia Carpenter
-- 2010-06-21T06:09:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/world-gold-council-augmentum-spend-18-7-million-for-bullionvault-stake.html

          
          
             The World Gold Council said it and
Augmentum Capital completed a 12.5 million pound ($18.7 million)
funding to invest in BullionVault in exchange for an equity
interest.  
 Tim Levene, partner at Augmentum, and Marcus Grubb,
managing director of investment at the World Gold Council, will
join the board of BullionVault, according to a statement today
on the World Gold Councilâ€™s website.  
          
          


  


        